{"questionId":"12405","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In a large population of hens, the weight of a hen is normally distributed with mean <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\mu \">\n  <mi>μ</mi>\n</math></span> kg&nbsp;and standard deviation <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sigma \">\n  <mi>σ</mi>\n</math></span> kg. A random sample of 100 hens is taken from the population.</p>\n<p>The mean weight for the sample is denoted by <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\bar X\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">¯</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the distribution of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\bar X\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">¯</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> giving its mean and variance.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\bar X \\sim N\\left( {\\mu {\\text{,}}\\,\\,\\frac{{{\\sigma ^2}}}{{100}}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo stretchy=\"false\">¯</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>∼</mo>\n  <mi>N</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>μ</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>,</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>σ</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mn>100</mn>\n        </mrow>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n</math></span> in place of 100.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12405","referenceCode":"19M.3.AHL.TZ0.Hsp_3a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"State the distribution of X ¯ giving its mean and variance.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.14—Linear transformation of a single RV, E(X) and VAR(X), unbiased estimators","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.15—Central limit theorem","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.16—Confidence intervals","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.18—T and Z test, type I and II errors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}